Citation.sTitle: Experimental and calculated liquid-liquid equilibrium data for water + furfural + solvents
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid-liquid equilibrium data for water + furfural + ethyl or propyl acetate are reported at 288.2, 303.2 and 318.2 K and atmospheric pressure (approx.. 95 kPa). The systems present type II phase diagrams, since water is partially miscible with furfural and esters. In order to obtain more general water+furfural interaction parameters, NRTL and UNIQUAC models were utilized to correlate data determined in this work and data for 11 systems previously reported. The models correlate well the obtained tie lines obtained and NRTL presents better performance than UNIQUAC.
